Package: normalize
Version: 0.7.3
Revision: 1
Source: http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~cvaill/%n/%n-%v.tar.bz2
SourceDirectory: %n-%v
Depends: mad-bin (>= 0.14.2b), mad-shlibs (>= 0.14.2b), audiofile-shlibs, glib-shlibs
BuildDepends: mad (>= 0.14.2b), audiofile, glib
ConfigureParams: --prefix=%p --exec-prefix=%p --disable-xmms --with-audiofile --with-audiofile-prefix=%p --libexecdir=%p/lib --mandir=%p/share/man
InstallScript: <<
  make install DESTDIR=%d
<<
DocFiles: COPYING INSTALL NEWS README THANKS TODO doc/frontend.txt
Description: An audio file volume normalizer
DescDetail: <<
Normalize is a tool for adjusting the volume of audio files to a standard level.
This is useful for things like creating mixed CD's and mp3 collections, where
different recording levels on different albums can cause the volume to vary 
greatly from song to song.
<<
